.TH "calc_block_sector" 9 "calc_block_sector" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
calc_block_sector \- Calculate blocks, pages and ofs.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" calc_block_sector
.BI "(loff_t from "  ","
.BI "int *block0 "  ","
.BI "int *block1 "  ","
.BI "int *page "  ","
.BI "int *ofs "  ","
.BI "int reliable "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "from" 12
offset in flash
.IP "block0" 12
first plane block index calculated
.IP "block1" 12
second plane block index calculated
.IP "page" 12
page calculated
.IP "ofs" 12
offset in page
.IP "reliable" 12
0 if docg3 in normal mode, 1 if docg3 in fast mode, 2 if docg3 in
reliable mode.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The calculation is based on the reliable/normal mode. In normal mode, the 64
pages of a block are available. In reliable mode, as pages 2*n and 2*n+1 are
clones, only 32 pages per block are available.
